    "industrial_process_notes": "Patented in 1941 by John Rex Whinfield and James Tennant Dickson (Calico Printers' Association); DuPont commercialized Dacron fiber in 1950 and Mylar film in 1951. Two main industrial routes: the DMT process (transesterification of dimethyl terephthalate with ethylene glycol) and the PTA process (direct esterification of terephthalic acid with ethylene glycol). ~31 million tonnes produced globally as of 2025.",
